  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0d9c\u0ddc\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0dc5\u0db8\u0dd4 \u0dc3\u0dad\u0dd2 3\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0d82\u0da0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0d9a \u0db4\u0dd0\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dab\u0dd3\u0dd2\u0db8  30000  \u0d89\u0d9a\u0dca\u0db8\u0dc0\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "In the first 3 weeks of August, tourist arrivals exceeded 30,000",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The number of tourists who came to Sri Lanka in the first three weeks of August has exceeded 30,000. According to the data of the Sri Lanka Tourism Development Authority, 31,105 tourists have come to Sri Lanka between August 1 and 23.",
        "From January 01 to August 23, 489,775 tourists have visited Sri Lanka. Average daily tourist arrivals for the month so far are around 1,350.",
        "Analysis of the weekly arrival trend for the month of August shows that the first week of the month (August 01-07) saw the highest number of tourists visit the country. The following weeks showed a downward trend.",
        "Total tourist arrivals in August were likely to be lower than in July at 47,293.",
        "The top three source markets for Sri Lanka for the month of August were UK, India and Germany. Between August 10 and 23, the number of arrivals from the United Kingdom was 5,872, while the total arrivals from India and Germany were 4,262 and 2,779 respectively."
      ],
